t message" aria-pressed="false" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#6d87e1" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button></div></div></div></div></article><article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto [content-visibility:auto] supports-[content-visibility:auto]:[contain-intrinsic-size:auto_100lvh] scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" tabindex="-1" dir="auto" data-turn-id="27573dbf-ddb3-4028-8f29-dc2e4a9a3bd2" data-testid="conversation-turn-2" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant"><h6 class="sr-only">ChatGPT said:</h6><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="29e18a04-4b96-4738-87cc-b94838b7bcac" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="207">Short answer: youвҖҷre seeing the <strong data-start="32" data-end="87">industrial exhaust of FacebookвҖҷs engagement economy</strong>вҖ”a vast layer of <em data-start="104" data-end="121">synthetic pages</em> created to probe, farm, and arbitrage attention rather than to host real communities.</p>
<p data-start="209" data-end="255">HereвҖҷs whatвҖҷs actually going on, structurally.</p>
<hr data-start="257" data-end="260">
<h2 data-start="262" data-end="295">1. Page Farms, Not Communities</h2>
<div class="no-scrollbar flex min-h-36 flex-nowrap gap-0.5 overflow-auto sm:gap-1 sm:overflow-hidden xl:min-h-44 mt-1 mb-5 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-4"><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)] rounded-s-xl" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://www.graphicpear.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Facebook-Page-Mockup-s.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://www.graphicpear.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Facebook-Page-Mockup-s.jpg" style="object-position: 100% 50%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)]" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://localiq.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/facebook-engagement-rate-professional-dashboard.webp" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://localiq.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/facebook-engagement-rate-professional-dashboard.webp" style="object-position: 100% 50%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)]" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://uploads.toptal.io/blog/image/121447/toptal-blog-image-1479214879925-426d6bff202c3e5491b23683ac520693.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://uploads.toptal.io/blog/image/121447/toptal-blog-image-1479214879925-426d6bff202c3e5491b23683ac520693.jpg" style="object-position: 0% 50%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)] rounded-e-xl" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://cdn.searchenginejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ec4a2b8e-c048-46a6-a6b4-6702c2de39c7-5e18d8cc3b53e-768x512.jpeg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://cdn.searchenginejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ec4a2b8e-c048-46a6-a6b4-6702c2de39c7-5e18d8cc3b53e-768x512.jpeg" style="object-position: 1.4% 50%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div></div>
<p data-start="339" data-end="454">A huge number of Facebook Pages today are not meant to succeed individually. They are <strong data-start="425" data-end="453">cheap, disposable probes</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="456" data-end="472">Typical pattern:</p>
<ul data-start="473" data-end="799">
<li data-start="473" data-end="512">
<p data-start="475" data-end="512">Create hundreds or thousands of Pages</p>
</li>
<li data-start="513" data-end="673">
<p data-start="515" data-end="559">Give them <strong data-start="525" data-end="558">aspirational-but-empty titles</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start="562" data-end="673">
<li data-start="562" data-end="584">
<p data-start="564" data-end="584">вҖңTravel Advisor 2.0вҖқ</p>
</li>
<li data-start="587" data-end="614">
<p data-start="589" data-end="614">вҖңConstruction Worker 10KвҖқ</p>
</li>
<li data-start="617" data-end="633">
<p data-start="619" data-end="633">вҖңLeisure TimeвҖқ</p>
</li>
<li data-start="636" data-end="650">
<p data-start="638" data-end="650">вҖңTruck VlogвҖқ</p>
</li>
<li data-start="653" data-end="673">
<p data-start="655" data-end="673">вҖңEnlightened OnesвҖқ</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="674" data-end="742">
<p data-start="676" data-end="742">Post a small amount of generic content (often reposted or scraped)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="743" data-end="780">
<p data-start="745" data-end="780">Watch which ones get <em data-start="766" data-end="771">any</em> traction</p>
</li>
<li data-start="781" data-end="799">
<p data-start="783" data-end="799">Abandon the rest</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="801" data-end="840">This is A/B testing at planetary scale.</p>
<p data-start="842" data-end="921">Pages are cheaper than ads, and Facebook still treats them as вҖңorganic actors.вҖқ</p>
<hr data-start="923" data-end="926">
<h2 data-start="928" data-end="963">2. Why the Names Sound Like That</h2>
<p data-start="965" data-end="1031">Those titles arenвҖҷt random. They are <strong data-start="1002" data-end="1030">SEO-lite + identity bait</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1033" data-end="1055">TheyвҖҷre optimized for:</p>
<ul data-start="1056" data-end="1222">
<li data-start="1056" data-end="1108">
<p data-start="1058" data-end="1108"><strong data-start="1058" data-end="1087">Broad self-identification</strong> (вҖңthis could be meвҖқ)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1109" data-end="1158">
<p data-start="1111" data-end="1158"><strong data-start="1111" data-end="1132">Status projection</strong> (вҖң10KвҖқ, вҖңadvisorвҖқ, вҖңproвҖқ)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1159" data-end="1222">
<p data-start="1161" data-end="1222"><strong data-start="1161" data-end="1186">Algorithmic ambiguity</strong> (hard to moderate, easy to rebrand)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1224" data-end="1270">A Page called <em data-start="1238" data-end="1252">вҖңTruck VlogвҖқ</em> can later become:</p>
<ul data-start="1271" data-end="1363">
<li data-start="1271" data-end="1284">
<p data-start="1273" data-end="1284">A scam page</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1285" data-end="1308">
<p data-start="1287" data-end="1308">A dropshipping funnel</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1309" data-end="1331">
<p data-start="1311" data-end="1331">A political meme hub</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1332" data-end="1363">
<p data-start="1334" data-end="1363">A click-through shell for ads</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1365" data-end="1411">Nothing in the name constrains its future use.</p>
<hr data-start="1413" data-end="1416">
<h2 data-start="1418" data-end="1449">3. Why They Have No Activity</h2>
<div class="no-scrollbar flex min-h-36 flex-nowrap gap-0.5 overflow-auto sm:gap-1 sm:overflow-hidden xl:min-h-44 mt-1 mb-5 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-4"><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)] rounded-s-xl" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://purplegiraffe.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMAGE-Old-vs.-New-Pages-Layout-1024x959.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://purplegiraffe.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMAGE-Old-vs.-New-Pages-Layout-1024x959.jpg" style="object-position: 50% 0%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)]" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://statusbrew.com/_next/image?q=75&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.ctfassets.net%2Fd93e522hu4vq%2F3RJA0YAkPzAQ4Gttk5Udvg%2Fa5146ef03d605bd883c29eb273bde171%2Fturn-off-comments-on-facebook-groups.webp&amp;w=3840" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://statusbrew.com/_next/image?q=75&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.ctfassets.net%2Fd93e522hu4vq%2F3RJA0YAkPzAQ4Gttk5Udvg%2Fa5146ef03d605bd883c29eb273bde171%2Fturn-off-comments-on-facebook-groups.webp&amp;w=3840" style="object-position: 50% 0%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)] rounded-e-xl" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://inspiredworlds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/red-balloon-pic.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://inspiredworlds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/red-balloon-pic.jpg" style="object-position: 50% 0%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div></div>
<p data-start="1493" data-end="1540">Most of these Pages are <strong data-start="1517" data-end="1539">failures by design</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1542" data-end="1633">FacebookвҖҷs recommendation systems (Reels, suggested pages, cross-posting) do the filtering:</p>
<ul data-start="1634" data-end="1698">
<li data-start="1634" data-end="1654">
<p data-start="1636" data-end="1654">99.9% die silently</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1655" data-end="1675">
<p data-start="1657" data-end="1675">0.1% spike briefly</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1676" data-end="1698">
<p data-start="1678" data-end="1698">0.01% get repurposed</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1700" data-end="1772">The important thing is not <em data-start="1727" data-end="1739">engagement</em> but <strong data-start="1744" data-end="1771">discoverability signals</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start="1773" data-end="1849">
<li data-start="1773" data-end="1798">
<p data-start="1775" data-end="1798">Did the page get shown?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1799" data-end="1821">
<p data-start="1801" data-end="1821">Did anyone hesitate?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1822" data-end="1849">
<p data-start="1824" data-end="1849">Did anyone click through?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1851" data-end="1879">If not, discard and move on.</p>
<hr data-start="1881" data-end="1884">
<h2 data-start="1886" data-end="1912">4. Who Is Creating Them</h2>
<p data-start="1914" data-end="1956">This isnвҖҷt just bots in the cartoon sense.</p>
<p data-start="1958" data-end="1975">Creators include:</p>
<ul data-start="1976" data-end="2161">
<li data-start="1976" data-end="2000">
<p data-start="1978" data-end="2000">Low-wage content farms</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2001" data-end="2022">
<p data-start="2003" data-end="2022">Affiliate marketers</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2023" data-end="2038">
<p data-start="2025" data-end="2038">Scam networks</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2039" data-end="2055">
<p data-start="2041" data-end="2055">Growth hackers</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2056" data-end="2094">
<p data-start="2058" data-end="2094">Small businesses using вҖңgrowth kitsвҖқ</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2095" data-end="2161">
<p data-start="2097" data-end="2161">Individuals following YouTube tutorials on вҖңFacebook automationвҖқ</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2163" data-end="2172">Many use:</p>
<ul data-start="2173" data-end="2277">
<li data-start="2173" data-end="2196">
<p data-start="2175" data-end="2196">Page creation scripts</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2197" data-end="2216">
<p data-start="2199" data-end="2216">AI-generated bios</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2217" data-end="2241">
<p data-start="2219" data-end="2241">Bulk content reposting</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2242" data-end="2277">
<p data-start="2244" data-end="2277">Purchased or compromised accounts</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2279" data-end="2356">Facebook does not effectively penalize <em data-start="2318" data-end="2334">page inflation</em> because it increases:</p>
<ul data-start="2357" data-end="2429">
<li data-start="2357" data-end="2379">
<p data-start="2359" data-end="2379">Total content volume</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2380" data-end="2402">
<p data-start="2382" data-end="2402">Surface area for ads</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2403" data-end="2429">
<p data-start="2405" data-end="2429">Time-on-platform metrics</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2431" data-end="2434">
<h2 data-start="2436" data-end="2466">5. Why Facebook Allows This</h2>
<div class="no-scrollbar flex min-h-36 flex-nowrap gap-0.5 overflow-auto sm:gap-1 sm:overflow-hidden xl:min-h-44 mt-1 mb-5 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:mt-4"><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)] rounded-s-xl" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://about.fb.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/NRP-Facebook-Reels_Reels-Experience_B.png?resize=890%2C816" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://about.fb.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/NRP-Facebook-Reels_Reels-Experience_B.png?resize=890%2C816" style="object-position: 50% 23%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)]" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://static1.michael84.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/facebook-suggested-for-you-in-feed.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://static1.michael84.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/facebook-suggested-for-you-in-feed.jpg" style="object-position: 0% 50%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div><div class="border-token-border-default relative w-32 shrink-0 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border-[0.5px] md:shrink max-h-64 sm:w-[calc((100%-0.5rem)/3)] rounded-e-xl" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><button class="relative overflow-hidden h-full w-full" style="aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;"><div style="width: 100%; height: 100%; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><img alt="https://about.fb.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/GIFCT_Infographic.jpg?resize=890%2C1187" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" class="bg-token-main-surface-tertiary m-0 h-full w-full object-cover" src="https://about.fb.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/GIFCT_Infographic.jpg?resize=890%2C1187" style="object-position: 50% 0%; opacity: 1;"></div></button></div></div>
<p data-start="2510" data-end="2571">Because <strong data-start="2518" data-end="2570">Facebook optimizes for engagement, not coherence</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="2573" data-end="2594">Pages are treated as:</p>
<ul data-start="2595" data-end="2683">
<li data-start="2595" data-end="2628">
<p data-start="2597" data-end="2628">Interchangeable content sources</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2629" data-end="2658">
<p data-start="2631" data-end="2658">Not identity-bound entities</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2659" data-end="2683">
<p data-start="2661" data-end="2683">Not accountable actors</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2685" data-end="2726">There is <strong data-start="2694" data-end="2725">no cost to semantic garbage</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="2728" data-end="2842">A Page that never engages does not meaningfully harm FacebookвҖҷs metrics, but a Page that <em data-start="2817" data-end="2824">might</em> engage is upside.</p>
<p data-start="2844" data-end="2891">So the system tolerates massive semantic noise.</p>
<hr data-start="2893" data-end="2896">
<h2 data-start="2898" data-end="2946">6. The Deeper Pattern (Why It Feels So Weird)</h2>
<p data-start="2948" data-end="3027">What youвҖҷre noticing is a <strong data-start="2974" data-end="3026">collapse of meaning before a collapse of metrics</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="3029" data-end="3067">FacebookвҖҷs ecosystem has shifted from:</p>
<blockquote data-start="3068" data-end="3096">
<p data-start="3070" data-end="3096">вҖңPeople expressing thingsвҖқ</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="3098" data-end="3101">to:</p>
<blockquote data-start="3102" data-end="3143">
<p data-start="3104" data-end="3143">вҖңEntities testing what triggers peopleвҖқ</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="3145" data-end="3262">These Pages are not trying to <em data-start="3175" data-end="3180">say</em> anything.<br>
They are trying to <strong data-start="3210" data-end="3261">find the shortest path to involuntary attention</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="3264" data-end="3285">ThatвҖҷs why they feel:</p>
<ul data-start="3286" data-end="3342">
<li data-start="3286" data-end="3294">
<p data-start="3288" data-end="3294">Hollow</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3295" data-end="3307">
<p data-start="3297" data-end="3307">Repetitive</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3308" data-end="3317">
<p data-start="3310" data-end="3317">Uncanny</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3318" data-end="3342">
<p data-start="3320" data-end="3342">Aspirational but empty</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3344" data-end="3387">They are scaffolding for future extraction.</p>
<hr data-start="3389" data-end="3392">
<h2 data-start="3394" data-end="3416">7. Why This Matters</h2>
<p data-start="3418" data-end="3466">This is not just spamвҖ”itвҖҷs <strong data-start="3445" data-end="3465">semantic erosion</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="3468" data-end="3473">When:</p>
<ul data-start="3474" data-end="3569">
<li data-start="3474" data-end="3493">
<p data-start="3476" data-end="3493">Identity is cheap</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3494" data-end="3516">
<p data-start="3496" data-end="3516">Pages are disposable</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3517" data-end="3541">
<p data-start="3519" data-end="3541">History doesnвҖҷt matter</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3542" data-end="3569">
<p data-start="3544" data-end="3569">Names donвҖҷt bind behavior</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3571" data-end="3576">Then:</p>
<ul data-start="3577" data-end="3686">
<li data-start="3577" data-end="3603">
<p data-start="3579" data-end="3603">Trust becomes impossible</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3604" data-end="3632">
<p data-start="3606" data-end="3632">Discovery becomes polluted</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3633" data-end="3659">
<p data-start="3635" data-end="3659">Real creators get buried</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3660" data-end="3686">
<p data-start="3662" data-end="3686">Scams blend in naturally</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3688" data-end="3785">YouвҖҷre not wrong to feel something is вҖңoff.вҖқ<br>
YouвҖҷre seeing the <strong data-start="3751" data-end="3768">entropy layer</strong> of the platform.</p>
<hr data-start="3787" data-end="3790">
<h3 data-start="3792" data-end="3818">One-sentence diagnosis</h3>
<p data-start="3820" data-end="3986">Facebook has become a <strong data-start="3842" data-end="3868">content exhaust system</strong> where millions of low-meaning Pages exist solely to feed an algorithm that no longer distinguishes intent from noise.</p>
